name: MIMO'S ANSWERS
description:
For an adopted child, answering the harder questions around their adoption story may be difficult. Some questions require a little thinking and understanding, but for author Chrissy Zaremba it shouldn't be.

This book contains an endearing account where a young girl beautifully and positively responds to difficult questions about adoption and her personal adoption story. For a child, answering the harder questions around their adoption story may be tricky, but it doesn't have to be.
Mimo’s Answers introduces possible answers or responses adopted children can use until they develop their own. Adoption is a wonderful bit unpredictable journey, and this book is to help empower adopted children to be able to talk about their special past and be ready for anything they may be asked.

Distinctly informative, inspirational and enhanced with beautiful illustrations by Jackie Frazer, an upcoming artist and graphic designer on the Sunshine Coast, this book will surely make a difference in the lives of the adopted children to become comfortable, confident and absolutely happy with who they are.

description:

This tank is made from a very soft jersey cotton material with its wide shoulders and deep free edge (seamless) sleeves, it is once again not only super dooper trendy but also mega comfy.
